1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 57-15 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to limitations on taxing district budgets without voter approval; and to
3 provide an effective date.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 57-15 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
6 and enacted as follows:
7 Limitation on taxing district budgets without voter approval.
8 1. Notwithstanding that a taxing district may have unused or excess levy authority under
9 any other provision of law, this section supersedes and limits that authority. This
10 section may not be interpreted as authority to increase any property tax levy authority
11 otherwise provided by law and must be applied to limi t the growth of a taxing district's
12 budge t . The governing body of a taxing district may not exceed the final budget of tha t
13 taxing district in the preceding taxable year by more than the consumer price index,
14 subject to the following:
15 a. When property and improvements to property which were not taxable in the
16 preceding taxable year are taxable in the current taxable year, the final budget of
17 the taxing district in the previous taxable year must be increased for purposes of
18 this section to reflect the taxes that would have been imposed against the
19 additional taxable valuation attributable to that property at the mill rate applied to
20 all property in the preceding taxable year.
21 b. When a property tax exemption existed in the preceding taxable year which has
22 been reduced or no longer exists for the current taxable year, the final budget of
23 the taxing district in the preceding taxable year must be increased for purposes of
24 this section to reflect the taxes that would have been imposed against the portion
